      "message": "\u003e I thought building another MinidumpFileWriter is simple, since\n\u003e - The document of MinidumpFileWriter::WriteEverything() doesn\u0027t mention the method could be called multiple times.\n\nYou are correct that you can’t WriteEverything() twice. But that’s not what I meant. I meant that if you already wrote the minidump to a file, don’t waste time building another (should-be-identical) minidump. Instead, open the existing, already-written minidump, and put that through your zlib-base94-log stream pipeline.\n\n\u003e What\u0027s your advice here?\n\u003e \n\u003e Is it OK to read the data from database, and delete the database record when handler shouldn\u0027t generate the report?\n\nI’m talking about the case where you want to _both_ write the minidump to the database _and_ log it. I’m not talking about writing to _only_ the database or _only_ the log.",
