      "side": 1,
      "message": "I checked the code again, the data source is moved to MinidumpFileWriter 😞,\n\nDo you think we can ignore the UserExtensionStream for log? It seemed there are two implementations of UserStreamDataSource (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/crashpad/crashpad/handler/user_stream_data_source.h?type\u003dcs\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d29), any critical information out there?\n\nIf we can\u0027t ignore it, MinidumpUserStreamWriter can cache the data from StreamDataSource in MinidumpUserStreamWriter::ExtensionStreamDataSourceRead(), and we can move MinidumpUserStreamWriter to another MinidumpFileWriter after the first MinidumpFileWriter write everything, is this a little hacky? \n\nAny suggestion?",
