      "message": "\u003e I checked the code again, the data source is moved to MinidumpFileWriter 😞,\n\u003e \n\u003e Do you think we can ignore the UserExtensionStream for log?\n\nPeople add them for a reason, so I don’t think so.\n\nThey’re not typically big, either.\n\n\u003e It seemed there are two implementations of UserStreamDataSource (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/crashpad/crashpad/handler/user_stream_data_source.h?type\u003dcs\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d29), any critical information out there?\n\u003e \n\u003e If we can\u0027t ignore it, MinidumpUserStreamWriter can cache the data from StreamDataSource in MinidumpUserStreamWriter::ExtensionStreamDataSourceRead(), and we can move MinidumpUserStreamWriter to another MinidumpFileWriter after the first MinidumpFileWriter write everything, is this a little hacky? \n\nToo hacky.\n\n\u003e Any suggestion?\n\nThis is exactly what I’m talking about. It becomes a non-issue if you would just build a minidump up one time and then reuse what’s on disk if you need it.",
