      "message": "\u003e Did you mean has adapter to stream the data to output stream?\n\nYes.\n\n\u003e I thought about it, but\n\u003e MinidumpFileWriter::WriteEverything() will jump back the begin of file and rewrite something, it seems not possible.\n\nRight. All we need to do is add a parameter to WriteEverything() to tell it that it’s streaming and won’t be able to rewind in a seek.\n\nThe rewind is only to write the magic number, so that when something’s being written to disk in the database, we don’t make it look like a valid minidump until everything’s been written. It’s OK to avoid that when we’re not writing to disk.",
